observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require:
a. The Municipal Accountant and Municipal General Services Officer to reconcile the discrepancies noted between the RPCPPE and accounting records and effect the adjustments to arrive at reconciled balances, and to maintain updated PCs and PPELCs as basis for reconciliation and validation;
b. The Municipal Accountant to draw a Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) to drop the small value property items from the books by debiting Prior Years’ Adjustment and Accumulated Depreciation and by crediting the respective PPE accounts;

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the Local
Council to fully utilize the budget for the LCPC, in compliance with RA No.
9344 and DILG Memorandum Circular No. 2012-120.

We also recommended that the Municipal Mayor advise the LCPC to
submit the following reports annually to the Office of the Auditor:

Council’s Annual Work and Financial Plan;
Local Development Plan for Children;
Local Code for Children;

Local State of Children’s Report;

Local Investment Plan for Children; and
Accomplishment Reports.
